rget yourself and sit down. The trick is, wait until you see your mana bar increase ever so slightly at the end of a tick. Immediately hit this hot key. You will stand and cast Inner Fire on your self, then sit down before the next tick, allowing you to actually gain the whole six second as if you were medding. The spell will recover just about the same time the mana bar increases, and you hit the button again.<br><br>I did not include a targeting line because you can easily use this same hot key to chain heal others during the low levels when this spell is useful, without changing the hot key. Simply target them then use the key.<br><br>It's a little boring, but considering the low mana cost of this spell, it's relative efficiency, and the fact that you are missing -zero- med time, there's little reason to use any other method to heal up, especially after mild fights. At my current level of 18, I can cast this spell maybe 20 times in ~ only one bubble as I am medding almost as much as the spell costs, plus the occasional medding through for fizzles or to retime my chain casting to fall within the tick (see 4 below).<br><br>A couple of simple things that may need adjustment. <br>1.) You may need to adjust the pause amount slightly. It should be about 28, give or take.<br>2.) set the cast line up to match the actual spell slot for Inner Fire. At level 18, I keep this one memmed because I use it all of the time.<br>3.) If the spell fizzles, do nothing. You will stand as normal, and sit just before the end of the turn and gain mana as if you never stood. Simply retry next round. But, you can again cast immediately after the end of the tick (see 4)<br>4.) As you cast this several times in a row, you will get closer and closer to still being standing at the end of a tick. No matter. Simply skip a tick, and restart the following tick, hitting the hot key immediately after the end of a tick and you will have a few more rounds of heals before you need to stay medding for an extra tick again.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm24.showPrevMessage?topicID=5.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm24.showNextMessage?topicID=5.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm24.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=5.topic&index=4><img src=http://www.brentcopeland.com/beastlord/images/messageboard/BL_add_reply2.jpg border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm24.emailToFriend?topicID=5.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm24.threadControl?topicID=5.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm24.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=5.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub115.ezboard.com/feqbeastlordfrm24.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=5.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub115.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="eqbeastlordfrm1">The Den<option value="eqbeastlordfrm2">General Spell Discussion<option value="eqbeastlordfrm3">Quests<option value="eqbeastlordfrm4">Levels 1 - 8<option value="eqbeastlordfrm6">Levels 9 - 14<option value="eqbeastlordfrm7">